Sentencas: Cathode materials of SrCo1-xGaxO3-delta (x=0, 0.1, 0.2, 0.3, 0.4) for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFC) were synthesized by an Ethylene Diamine Tetraacetic Acid (EDTA)-citrate complexing method.
Titulo: Preparation and Performance of SrCo1-xGaxO3-δ Cathode Materials for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The obtained samples were characterized by X-ray diffraction, thermal expansion measurement, X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy, and the effects of Ga-doping on performance and properties of materials were evaluated.
Titulo: Preparation and Performance of SrCo1-xGaxO3-δ Cathode Materials for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The results show that all the samples have brownmillerite structure.
Titulo: Preparation and Performance of SrCo1-xGaxO3-δ Cathode Materials for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The thermal expansion coefficient (TEC), electrical conductivity and the amount of adsorbed oxygen on the surface of the cathode materials gradually decrease with Ga content increasing.
Titulo: Preparation and Performance of SrCo1-xGaxO3-δ Cathode Materials for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Among the as-abtained samples, SrCo0 8Ga0.2O3-delta shows the lowest area specific resistance (ASR) of 0.73 Omega.cm(2) at 600 degrees C, the single-cell with it as cathode demonstrates a maximum power density of 0.484 W/cm(2) at 650 degrees C.
Titulo: Preparation and Performance of SrCo1-xGaxO3-δ Cathode Materials for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
